    {
      "question": "The pair of equations $x + 2y = 5$ and $3x + ky + 15 = 0$ represents parallel lines. What is the value of $k$?",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The condition for parallel lines is $a_1/a_2 = b_1/b_2 \\neq c_1/c_2$.",
          "Here, $a_1=1, b_1=2, c_1=-5$ and $a_2=3, b_2=k, c_2=15$.",
          "Set the ratio $a_1/a_2 = b_1/b_2$: $1/3 = 2/k$.",
          "Solve for $k$: $k = 6$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$1/3 = 2/k \\\\ k = 3 \\times 2 \\\\ k = 6$"
