    {
      "question": "If the pair of equations $2x + 3y = 7$ and $(a+b)x + (2a-b)y = 21$ has infinitely many solutions, then which of the following is true?",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "For infinitely many solutions, $a_1/a_2 = b_1/b_2 = c_1/c_2$.",
          "$2/(a+b) = 3/(2a-b) = 7/21 = 1/3$.",
          "From $2/(a+b) = 1/3$, $a+b = 6$.",
          "From $3/(2a-b) = 1/3$, $2a-b = 9$.",
          "Adding equations: $3a = 15 \\Rightarrow a=5, b=1$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a+b=6 \\\\ 2a-b=9 \\\\ 3a=15 \\\\ a=5, b=1$"
