      "question": "For what value of $p$ is the system $px + 3y = 7$ and $2x + 6y = 14$ inconsistent?",
      "answer": "(D)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Inconsistent means no solution, so $a_1/a_2 = b_1/b_2 \\neq c_1/c_2$.",
          "$p/2 = 3/6 \\neq 7/14$.",
          "$p/2 = 1/2 \\Rightarrow p = 1$.",
          "Check the third ratio: $1/2 \\neq 1/2$ is false (they are equal).",
          "Since $1/2 = 1/2 = 1/2$, the lines are coincident (infinitely many solutions) for $p=1$. Therefore, no value of $p$ makes it inconsistent."
        ],
        "derivation": "$p/2 = 3/6 = 7/14 \\\\ p/2 = 1/2 \\\\ p = 1 \\\\ \\text{But } 1/2 = 1/2 \\text{ means infinite solutions. No } p \\text{ exists.}"
